<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-24T07:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-24T07:35:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/1143: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ford</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-24T16:00:00+03:25">May
                                        24, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 24—2:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>366. My 359 May 22. Millspaugh and I both feel that note suggested in
                                Department’s 303 May 17, should be presented at once before he and I
                                have our next interview together with Prime Minister. I hope
                                therefore Department will telegraph authorization urgently.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>